  "informal_statement": "For every natural number n, 2^n is at least 1 -- powers of two are always positive (in fact >= 1).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Induction on n: the base case 2^0 = 1 >= 1 is immediate. In the successor step, rewrite 2^(n+1) via pow_succ to 2^n * 2; since the inductive hypothesis gives 2^n >= 1, omega closes 2^n * 2 >= 1 directly.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem one_le_two_pow (n : ℕ) : 1 ≤ 2 ^ n",
